                                        <!-- Question Text -->
                                        <div class="col-12 col-md-11">
                                            <p class="mb-3">I'm trying to center a div element on a webpage using CSS.
                                                I've tried several methods including flexbox and margin: auto, but
                                                nothing seems to work correctly. I want the div to be centered both
                                                horizontally and vertically on the page.</p>

                                            <p class="mb-3">Here's my current code:</p>

                                            <pre style="background: #f4f5f6; padding: 12px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>&lt;div class="container"&gt;
    &lt;div class="centered"&gt;Content&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

.container {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100vh;
}

.centered {
    margin: auto;
}</code></pre>

                                            <p class="mb-3">The div isn't centering. What am I doing wrong?</p>

